# EventHive Tool: Sponsor Deliverables Tracker

## Architecture
- Single self-contained HTML file (`tool.html`) — all CSS and JS inline
- No external dependencies, no build step, no framework
- Must work when opened directly in a browser with no server
- Under 500KB total file size

## Config System
- `EVENTHIVE_CONFIG = {}` object in a script tag — replaced at serve time on EventHive
- `{{config.propertyName}}` Mustache placeholders in HTML — replaced at serve time
- NEVER use `{{config.x}}` inside `<script>` tags — only in HTML attributes/text
- Config schema defined in `manifest.json` — keep both in sync

## Data Storage
- localStorage key: `eventhive_event_{eventSlug}_sponsors`
- Always check if data exists before rendering (fresh state = no data)
- Provide sample/demo data mode for first-time users

## EventHive Integration
- Reads from EventHive's tool data API when `EVENTHIVE_CONFIG.__hosted === true`
- Falls back to localStorage when not hosted
- `EVENTHIVE_CONFIG.__apiBase` provides the API base URL in hosted mode
- Always implement both storage paths for maximum compatibility

## Coding Standards
- Vanilla JS only — no React, no Vue, no jQuery
- Tailwind-style utility classes are fine if defined inline in `<style>`
- Use semantic HTML where possible
- Mobile-responsive (test at 375px width minimum)
- All user-visible strings in English (i18n is a future concern)
- Colours from `EVENTHIVE_CONFIG.primaryColor` for theming — never hardcode brand colours

## Testing
- Open `tool.html` in browser, verify all interactions work
- Test with localStorage cleared (fresh state — empty screen should be graceful)
- Test with sample data populated
- Test at mobile width (375px) and desktop (1200px)

## File Size Budget
- Target under 400KB
- Inline all CSS and JS — no external requests except optional CDN for icons
- If adding a library, consider if vanilla JS can do the same job
